<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id8f280752-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s1964"><num value="1964">§ 1964.</num><heading> Report to Congress</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The President shall whenever appropriate report to the Congress his action hereunder.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id8f280753-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">(<ref href="/us/pl/85/7/s5">Pub. L. 85–7, § 5</ref>, <date date="1957-03-09">Mar. 9, 1957</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/71/6">71 Stat. 6</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/87/195">Pub. L. 87–195</ref>, pt. IV, § 705, <date date="1961-09-04">Sept. 4, 1961</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/75/463">75 Stat. 463</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id8f280754-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id8f280755-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id8f280756-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1961—<ref href="/us/pl/87/195">Pub. L. 87–195</ref> substituted “whenever appropriate” for “within the months of January and July of each year”.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="id8f280757-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="repeals" id="id8f280758-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Repeals</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0"><ref href="/us/pl/87/195/s705">Section 705 of Pub. L. 87–195</ref>, cited as a credit to this section, was repealed by <ref href="/us/pl/87/565/s401">section 401 of Pub. L. 87–565</ref>, pt. IV, <date date="1962-08-01">Aug. 1, 1962</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/76/263">76 Stat. 263</ref>, except insofar as section 705 affected this section.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
